Patch B — Authority as Redundant Slot

(Pool Selection + Fallback Chain)

B1. Purpose

Tier III “single decider” authority must never imply “hero leadership.”
It is a latency-compression slot drawn from a redundant pool.

B2. Authority Pool Minimum

Each Dunbar-scale cell must maintain:

≥ 5 authority-eligible citizens available for invocation rotation


This minimum is a survivability constraint.

A cell without redundancy is structurally fragile.

B3. Selection Rule (Slot Pull)

When Tier III authority is required:

the system selects a decider from the eligible pool based on:

current regulation / readiness

role-skill match

recent invocation load (cooldown)

proximity / availability

conflict-of-interest constraints



Popularity, charisma, and ambition are disallowed selection signals.

B4. Fallback Chain (If No Fit Decider)

If no pool member can accept (or is fit):

1. Invoke local council to select a decider (adds latency but preserves safety)


2. Query adjacent cell pool (mutual aid redundancy)


3. Escalate to regional council (only if scope exceeds local containment)



This preserves continuity without permanent rulers.


