Summary Constraint

> Slow harm is addressed by care-side intervention, not pre-emptive coercion.
Authority is a redundant slot, not a ruler.
Refusal is telemetry, not defect.
Catastrophic continuity exists, but dissolves immediately.



If any of these patches create permanent power, conditional care, or surveillance coercion, they are incorrectly implemented.
